Just wondering if anybody else on this list is planning on attending
GECCO 2005 in Washington DC.  Philip and I are planning on attending,
and we're hoping to submit a paper for the regular paper deadline in
mid-January.

We're working on fingerprint classification now, automatically
categorizing fingerprints into one of four classes: whorl, left loop,
right loop, or arch (and for the five-class problem, tented arch). 
Automatic classification of fingerprints is a pretty difficult
problem, and is hard to do quickly and accurately.

We're in the early stages of experimenting in this domain, but we've
already evolved a network that can distinguish two distinct left loop
prints from two of each of the other classes, so we're pretty
optimistic.

Derek
